================================================================================
PART 15: FINAL TIPS FOR DEVELOPERS
================================================================================

1. USE THE TECHNICAL TERM
   If you know the concept name (Mutex, Circuit Breaker, Memoization),
   use it. The AI will instantly treat you as an expert and respond
   accordingly.

2. IF YOU DON'T KNOW THE TERM
   Ask: "What is the engineering term for when I want to stop my app
   from calling a broken API?"
   Answer: "Circuit Breaker"
   Then use that keyword in your actual prompt.

3. COMBINE KEYWORDS FROM MULTIPLE CATEGORIES
   Role + Task + Quality + Security + Format = Powerful prompt

4. USE CHAIN-OF-THOUGHT FOR COMPLEX PROBLEMS
   Add "Let's think step by step" for math, logic, and debugging.

5. ITERATE
   First draft is rarely perfect. Refine with follow-up keywords:
   "Make it more concise"
   "Add error handling"
   "Show edge cases"

6. BE SPECIFIC
   "Refactor"  "Apply Extract Method to the validation logic"
   "Optimize"  "Reduce time complexity to O(n log n)"
   "Test"  "Write unit tests covering happy path and null inputs"


================================================================================
END OF COMPLETE PROMPT ENGINEERING REFERENCE
================================================================================

You now have the complete vocabulary from Beginner to Architect level.
The "keyword" to unlock the next level is simply knowing the NAME of
what you want. Use these terms, and AI will respond like a colleague.

================================================================================
